# stale-documentation-audits-and-sync — History

## v1.0.0 (2026-05-18) — Merge of 12 skills

**Changed by:** Skill-merge swarm (Phase C Wave 2, M17 / #1780)
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed

Consolidated 12 stale-doc audit and sync skills into this canonical skill.
Covers: Future Improvements drift, stale numeric counts, metric discrepancy fixes,
agent/file count drift, ecosystem role drift detection, multi-file ecosystem sync,
workflow README audits, doc contradiction resolution, cross-doc citation drift defenses,
and implementation-lag doc sync.

---

## Superseded from doc-stale-future-improvements-audit

```yaml
name: doc-stale-future-improvements-audit
description: Systematically audit design docs for Future Improvements sections that
  describe features already implemented in source code.
category: documentation
date: 2026-02-22
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: true
```

Systematically audit all design docs for "Future Improvements" sections listing features
already implemented in source code. Five-phase workflow: discover candidate sections (grep),
cross-reference against source (ls + head), categorize findings, apply fixes, commit and PR.

Key observations: ASCII diagrams go stale faster than tables; "implemented but not integrated"
is a valid intermediate state; raw run archives are not design docs.

Verified on: ProjectScylla Issue #880 (follow-up from #759), PR #989.

