## Superseded from sync-stale-future-improvements

```yaml
name: sync-stale-future-improvements
description: Sync stale Future Improvements sections with actual implementation.
category: documentation
date: 2026-02-20
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
```

Six-step workflow: confirm implementation exists (grep), read stale docs, add proper
documented section near the component, remove stale numbered list item, scan remaining
Future Improvements systematically, commit and PR.

Key insight: when issue asks to check other Future Improvements for staleness, do it
systematically — grep every item in source before concluding it's still future work.

Verified on: ProjectScylla Issue #759, PR #877.

