## Superseded from fix-doc-metric-discrepancies

```yaml
name: fix-doc-metric-discrepancies
description: Fix stale or incorrect metric values in documentation (test counts, coverage
  thresholds, command paths) that drift from actual codebase state.
category: documentation
date: 2026-02-27
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: true
```

Four-phase workflow: audit actual values (pytest --collect-only, grep fail_under),
cross-reference against CLAUDE.md / README / pyproject.toml, apply minimal targeted fixes
(Edit tool, exact string replacement), verify and commit.

Key observations: worktree branches may already have partial fixes (always read before
editing); use `+` suffix for forward-compatibility on counts; exact subtest counts
should not have `+`; `--cov` path must match installed package name.

Verified on: ProjectScylla Issue #1112, PR #1150 (3,185 tests, 78.36% coverage).

