## Superseded from documentation-ecosystem-role-drift-detection

```yaml
name: documentation-ecosystem-role-drift-detection
description: Reconcile stale ecosystem role descriptions with actual implementation.
category: documentation
date: 2026-03-25
version: "1.0.0"
user-invocable: false
tags: [documentation, ecosystem, drift-detection, ablation, reconciliation]
```

Five-step workflow: build alignment matrix (audit every role-mentioning file), decide
update-docs vs add-code (update docs when zero implementation exists for stale claim),
make minimal doc fix (often only ONE bullet), create ADR in docs/dev/adr/, add
parametrized drift-detection pytest (18 cases: 5 forbidden patterns × 3 docs + 3
canonical checks), file cross-repo issues for external docs.

Decision rule: Does codebase have ANY code for stale claim? → If zero, update docs.
Is codebase purpose-built for current role? → Update docs to match reality.

Failed: no failed approaches; decision was straightforward (69K lines ablation code,
zero chaos code).

Verified on: ProjectScylla Issue #1503, PR #1547.

