## Superseded from documentation-multi-file-ecosystem-sync

```yaml
name: documentation-multi-file-ecosystem-sync
description: Synchronize ecosystem repository listings across multiple documentation
  files using GitHub API as source of truth.
category: documentation
date: 2026-03-25
version: "1.0.0"
user-invocable: false
verification: verified-precommit
tags: [documentation, ecosystem, multi-file-sync, github-api]
```

Five-step workflow: verify repo list against GitHub org API (gh api orgs/\<ORG\>/repos
--paginate), locate all ecosystem listing sites (grep across CLAUDE.md, README, docs,
.claude/agents/), build canonical table (alphabetical, under 80 chars per cell), apply same
table to all locations with consistent column headers, run pre-commit.

Consistency rules: same column headers (`Repository | Role`), same descriptions per repo,
mark current project with "(this project)" suffix.

Failed: Edit .claude/agents/ in worktree (permission denied) → note for follow-up;
Edit before Read → always Read target files first.

Verified on: ProjectScylla Issue #1507, PR #1551 (3→12 repos).

