## Superseded from workflow-readme-audit

```yaml
name: workflow-readme-audit
description: Audit .github/workflows/README.md against actual files on disk,
  update inventory to match reality, and document remaining duplication.
category: documentation
date: 2026-03-07
version: 1.1.0
user-invocable: true
absorbed: [workflow-readme-migration-sync]
```

Six-phase workflow: establish ground truth (ls .github/workflows/*.yml), read each
undocumented workflow (first 20 lines for name:/on:/paths:), audit inline duplication
(grep -rl), rewrite README summary table with shell verification command, fix markdownlint
failures (MD031/MD040 closing fences, MD013 line length, MD029 ordered list numbering),
commit and PR.

Post-migration sync (absorbed from workflow-readme-migration-sync): verify migration
complete before touching README; identify all 6 stale README locations; apply targeted
edits to description bullets, "Remaining Duplication" section, pattern examples,
"Adding New Workflows" checklist, and audit commands.

Failed: `pixi run npx markdownlint-cli2` (npx not in PATH; takes >2 min) → use
`git commit` to trigger pre-commit hook; closing fences with `text` on same line
→ use bare ` ``` `; `replace_all: false` for repeated phrases → use `replace_all: true`.

Verified on: ProjectOdyssey Issue #3344, PR #3978 (22 workflows); Issue (post-migration),
PR #4847.

