## Superseded from doc-contradiction-resolution

```yaml
name: doc-contradiction-resolution
description: "Skill: Resolve Documentation Contradictions Between Project Files"
category: documentation
date: 2026-03-19
version: "1.0.0"
user-invocable: false
```

Six-step workflow: identify contradiction (grep both files), determine canonical policy
(CLAUDE.md > .claude/shared/ > CONTRIBUTING.md), check all related files, make minimal
fix (only edit wrong file; never modify canonical source), verify no regressions, commit
and PR.

Key insight: always check `.claude/shared/pr-workflow.md` as a third possible location
for contradictions; in this case it was already clean.

Pre-commit behavior for Markdown-only changes: Python/YAML/Shell linters skipped;
Markdown Lint, Trailing Whitespace, End of Files, Large Files, Mixed Line Endings pass.

Verified on: ProjectScylla Issue #758, PR #871.

