## Superseded from doc-sync-existing-impl

```yaml
name: doc-sync-existing-impl
description: Sync documentation when an issue's fix is already implemented but docs
  lag behind.
category: documentation
date: 2026-03-15
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
```

Five-step workflow: confirm fix already exists (ls wrapper script, grep pre-commit
config entry, ls dev docs), find stale doc text (grep CLAUDE.md for old behavior),
make targeted edits (2 Edit calls typically sufficient), verify no markdown lint issues
(awk 'length > 120'), commit and PR.

Trigger symptoms: issue says "investigate/document" rather than "implement";
`.pre-commit-config.yaml` entry disagrees with CLAUDE.md description; existing
`docs/dev/` file already covers the problem completely.

Failed: skill invocation for commit (permission denied) → fall back to manual
`git add && git commit && git push && gh pr create`.

Verified on: ProjectOdyssey Issue #3365, PR #4894.
